==============================================================================
RUSTYBOX DUAL-EDITION LICENSING MODEL
==============================================================================

Rustybox is distributed under a dual-edition licensing model to offer maximum
flexibility for developers, enterprise environments, and embedded devices.
The project is split into two distinct editions compiled from the same workspace:

1. RUSTYBOX CORE (Permissive MIT Edition)
   - Binary Target: `rustybox-core`
   - Crate Path: `crates/rustybox-core`
   - License: MIT License (see Section A below)
   - Scope: Consists of 85+ applets implemented entirely using safe, permissive
     Rust libraries (e.g., uutils/coreutils, ripgrep libs, RustCrypto).
     No copyleft code (BusyBox C code) is compiled into this binary.

2. RUSTYBOX FULL (Copyleft GPL-2.0 Edition)
   - Binary Target: `rustybox`
   - Crate Path: Root crate
   - License: GNU General Public License, Version 2 (see Section B below)
   - Scope: Includes all 300+ applets, compiling both the permissive Rust
     re-implementations and the legacy transpiled BusyBox C codebase (via c2rust).
     As a derivative work of BusyBox, this combined binary falls under GPL-2.0.

